name: Puerto Rician Stone Petroglyph Tower
description:
Footlong recently made a trip to Puerto Rico with her parents to visit her Puerto Rican family and explore the islands for the first time.  One of her favorite stops was to look at the stone towers on some of the beaches.  She wanted to recreate the experience with this artwork.  

Footlong is and 11 year old artist and does not have a Twitter.  Contact art mentor Lily White on Twitter @rblbab with any questions.

This artwork will be added to the #HENjackpot community event.
